abstract: WITH the increase of good-fellowship between France and England, talk of tunneling the English Channel, thereby forming a new bond between the two countries, has been revived. During the recent sojourn of the London County Council in Paris its members inspected the model of a tunnel entirely new. The distinctive feature of the new scheme is that the tunnel is carried into the cliffs, well above the sea, on each side of the Channel.

abstract: WASHINGTON, March 3. -- Mrs. Roosevelt, according to the well-informed, will observe a quiet Lenten season. No guests at the White House are expected till Easter. This period of rest will be most welcome to all the Presidential household. abstract: PITTSBURG, Penn., March 2. -- There is considerable waiting among iron and steel consumers for lower prices in some lines. This is true of foundry pig iron, gray forge, and basic iron. It is the belief that production has about caught up to the consumption. This will compel furnace operators to either sell at a lower price or to stack their surplus iron.

abstract: The last Sunday concert of the New York Symphony Orchestra's series (to be repeated to-morrow evening) was given yesterday afternoon. abstract: After three days and three nights in the hands of kidnappers, Antonio Bozzuffi, the 14-year-old son of John Bozzuffi, banker, of Sixty-third Street and First Avenue, obtained his freedom yesterday and returned home to tell his story. abstract: Suppose as an extreme outcome of the popular agitation now in vogue, that the coaler railroads should be required by law to divorce themselves from their coal properties -- then what? abstract: The newest thing in paper is the disappearing kind. Soused in diluted sulphuric acid and then carefully glazed, it looks like the paper that abideth; but slowly the acid nibbles at the fibres under the glazing, till in a week or so the substance has clean gone out of it and the place thereof knows it no more. A most convenient sort of paper -- when you're the one to use it.

abstract: ATLANTA, Ga., March 9. -- Crazed by jealousy caused by her husband's attentions to Chappell Whisenant, her seventeen-year-old sister, Mrs. Edward M. Standifer, 25 years old, shot the girl dead this morning at the home of her brother-in-law, P.W. Dunham, with whose family Miss Whisenant resided. abstract: A traders' market, which this seems to be, is full of petty and unworthy deceptions. abstract: Only yesterday I had occasion to pity in Broadway a beautiful pair of horses, whose bearing reins were so tight that they were almost unable to move their heads. abstract: CHICAGO, March 19. -- Edward W. Gardner of Passaic, N.J., is the amateur billiard champion of America. He won the title to-night at the Chicago Athletic Association in the final game of the National tournament, which has been in progress for a week. His opponent tonight was J.F. Poggenburg of Liederkranz Club of New York, and the new champion won by the score of 300 to 265. Gardner played five games without a defeat.

abstract: LOUISVILLE, Ky., March 22. -- To-day's developments in bowling circles seem to indicate a hopeless split between the East and the West as a result of the defeat yesterday of Philadelphia for the next convention of the American Bowling Congress. abstract: CHICAGO, Ill., March 22. -- C.M. abstract: Two hotly contested matches in the second round of the hand tennis tournament at the New York Athletic Club yesterday resulted in W.A. Burke and J.H. Haslin coming through winners. abstract: Another attempt to kidnap Antonio Bozzuffi, the 15-year-old son of a well-to-do Italian banker, was made last night by three Italians. abstract: LONDON, March 25. -- The cotton market was strong all last week. The American product was in strong demand, and sales were interfered with somewhat by the difficulty of obtaining fine, serviceable spinning qualities at relatively reasonable figures. abstract: The games of the Catholic Athletic League under the auspices of St. Ann's Junior Holy Name Society, at the Twelfth Regiment Armory, Sixty-second Street and Columbus Avenue, last evening, were an unqualified success. The field of entries, representing over thirty churches, was so extensive as to occupy nearly three hours of preliminary heats before the finals were reached. The games were splendidly contested, expeditiously run, and developed some excellent contests and creditable performances.

abstract: ANDY ADAMS, whose "Log of a Cowboy" won such well-deserved recognition as an account of the vanished life of the Western cattleman as it really was, is the author of a new series of sketches of the same life just published by Houghton, Mifflin  Co. with the title "Cattle Brands." The merit of Mr. Adams's work lies not at all in any literary skill of wording or presentation.

abstract: As a result of the condition of the building occupied by the Morrisania Court the prisoners usually arraigned in that court were yesterday arraigned in the Westchester Court, in Main Street, Westchester. The Morrisania Court House has been closed by order of the Building Department of the Bronx, and will remain closed until repairs deemed advisable by that department have been made.
